description:
I waited to share this post because I had a bit of hope that #dictator Dan extension plan could have been stopped but obviously political interests have been prioritised over Taxpayers and Citizens request to stop this mad #lockdown .
After this shamble of vote today, I have to share this post. 
There will be a massive march on the 5th of September in Melbourne against the lockdown that Dan and his little MPs are forcing upon us.
I am not inviting anyone to participate and I am not one of the organizers but they have all my respect for risking their freedom for something they believe in and 10 of 1000s of Melbournians believe in.
Too many friends and families have been divided, too many business shut down, too much power to an embarrassment of a Premier and to Victoria Police with cops harassing and arresting Citizens, the same Taxpayer who pay their wage.
Extending the power of the premier is wrong, using lies to obtain that power is CRIMINAL.
Police should not harass people for sharing this, the protest has been made public by MSM and the police itself, more people know it because of them than because of social media.
Expressing our dissent is one of the pillars of DEMOCRACY certainly an obscure word for every party on the left side #Labor and #Greens
